@REMARK **********************************************************************
@NODE l_about "The purpose of this database"

Hi folks!

This Database contains dumps for the Synthesizer Korg 01/W. I collected some
from different @{"sources" LINK l_infos} and wrote the corresponding dump lists. Here is a
description of the directory structure:

@{u}Directory@{uu}   @{u}Contents@{uu}
data        dumps (*.dmp) and their descriptions (*.txt)
midi        MIDI files (need 01/W dumps) and a list of them (Songs.txt)
songs       sequences (*.seq,*.syx) to dump into the 01/W
            and a list of them (Songs.txt)

The lists are saved in plain ASCII format, so that you can easily print them
out (no AmigaGuide tags). There's another Korg-Database on the net, but since
I "only" have an AMIGA, this stuff is usefull just for people who have a PC
with Microsoft Windows and Microsoft Access.  :-(  O.K., this guide is also
just for people having AmigaGuide, BUT you don't need this guide to use the
dumps and read the contents lists!

So far, this database contains only few data. If you want to have your dumps
and its lists in it, send them to @{"me" LINK l_address} so that this database will grow and
everybody could benefit of it!
             
  I hope, I'm not the only one using it!

Please send emails/letters/01W-dumps/MIDI-stuff for the AMIGA/etc. to @{"me" LINK l_address}!
@{i}
By the way: does anybody need a Steinberg Pro 24 Sequenzer for the AMIGA?
It works perfectly with OS 1.3 (on 68000) and OS 3.1 (on 68030) on my good
old A1000.  :-)  In case you are interested and are willing to pay DM 199,-
for it, contact @{"me" LINK l_address}.
@{ui}
@ENDNODE
